{
  "texts": [
    "This point in humanity's technological progress is unprecedented, as interaction with such agents allows users to derive instant, effortless insight, assistance in self-reflection, knowledge synthesis, and any number of other cognitive tasks.",
    "In 1960, J. C. R. Licklider, the grandfather of the World Wide Web and one of the founding fathers of the ARPANet project, outlined the future of machine intelligence, asserting that the new age of computing would see what he termed \"mancomputer symbiosis\" (Licklider, 1960).",
    "A large 2019 literature review on the trend of AI over time concluded with the following: \".",
    "AI will tend to be more extensive and generalized.",
    "The emergence of intelligent systems means the innovation of traditional mechanisms, from human to machine collaboration\" (Lu, 2019)."
  ]
}